<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 29 at 5:23PM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern Oldham
and northwestern Deaf Smith Counties through 615 PM CDT...
At 523 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles east of Glenrio, or 27 miles west of Vega, moving northeast at
25 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Adrian and Glenrio.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
